    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_4147314385" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4147314385" />
    <a title="Anthony Watt" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/68427027-anthony-watt"><img alt="Anthony Watt" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4147314385?book_show_action=true">Aug 01, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anthony Watt" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anthony Watt" href="/user/show/68427027-anthony-watt">Anthony Watt</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4147314385" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13680188273558298170">Wow. I picked up this book after finishing a meaning of life course on Audible. This book really compliments that course well. I had very little understanding of Native American culture, beliefs or ways of life before reading this book. I would say I only have a very loose understanding of some of those areas now even after reading it right through. <br/><br/>The core message that resonates with me is why is western civilisation (an beyond) living at such a disconnected distance from nature? Why do we liv</span>
  <span id="freeText13680188273558298170" style="display:none">Wow. I picked up this book after finishing a meaning of life course on Audible. This book really compliments that course well. I had very little understanding of Native American culture, beliefs or ways of life before reading this book. I would say I only have a very loose understanding of some of those areas now even after reading it right through. <br /><br />The core message that resonates with me is why is western civilisation (an beyond) living at such a disconnected distance from nature? Why do we live in separated house boxes? Why don’t we live in smaller, closer communities? Why do we not value the natural world and see ourselves as part of it?<br /><br />There seems to be a gap between ancient wisdom and modern technologically advanced life. The two can exist together in harmony if only we choose to think a little differently and assess what truly matters. If nothing else this book challenges us to think differently and perhaps take some aspects of Native American thinking into our own heads.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13680188273558298170" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

